This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing and information retrieval, which is reflected in the focus on conversation systems and text matching. Specifically, the use of bag-of-words representations and mutual coverage between query and bag suggest a focus on text-based approaches to information retrieval. This aligns with the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
